SIMPLE: alike
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Alike
<hw>A*like"</hw> <pr>(⟦adot⟧*l⟦imac⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>onl⟦imac⟧c</ets>, <ets>gel⟦imac⟧c</ets>; pref. <ets>⟦amac⟧</ets> +
<ets>like</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having resemblance or similitude; similar;
without difference.</def> <mark>[Now used only
predicatively.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The darkness and the light are both <qex>alike</qex> to thee.</q>
<rj><qau>Ps. cxxxix. 12.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alike</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Alike
<hw>A*like"</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>gel⟦imac⟧ce</ets>,
<ets>onl⟦imac⟧ce</ets>.]</ety> <def>In the same manner, form, or degree;
in common; equally; <as>as, we are all <ex>alike</ex> concerned in
religion</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alike-minded</ent>⟦br⟧
